Required Python Libraries:
requests
fabric

$easy_install requests
$easy_install fabric

Configuration files:

/ebi/www/jlive/servers/tc-thornton/tomcat-7/conf/Catalina/localhost
/ebi/www/jlive/servers/tc-thornton/tomcat-8/conf/Catalina/localhost
with the name 

thornton-srv#software#ecblastws.xml


Follow these command for deploying this application on the server.

The Commands are :

scp ecblastws.war tomcat-7:
ssh tomcat-7
become tc_user
cd /ebi/www/jlive/servers/tc-thornton
./controller stop
ssh tomcat-8
become tc_user
cd /ebi/www/jlive/servers/tc-thornton
./controller stop
rm -rf tomcat-{7,8}/webapps/thornton-srv/software/ecblastws
cp ~asad/ecblastws.war /ebi/www/jlive/deploy/tc-thornton/
./controller start

these steps are:

1) create the jarfile
2) copy to (one of) the servers
3) go to the server
4) become the tc user
5) move to the directory where the controller script is
6) stop the controller
7) remove the current directories of code
8) copy the new war file to the 'deploy' dir
9) restart

The tricky part is that steps 3-6 are repeated on both machines.

test:
http://tc-test-3.ebi.ac.uk:9950/thornton-srv/software/ecblastws/

production:
http://tomcat-7.ebi.ac.uk:9950/thornton-srv/software/ecblastws/
http://tomcat-8.ebi.ac.uk:9950/thornton-srv/software/ecblastws/
